<title>FRANCE: FRENCH ELECTION - LATEST OPINION POLLS.</title>
<headline>FRENCH ELECTION - LATEST OPINION POLLS.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Following are the results of opinion polls conducted</p>
<p>since President Jacques Chirac dissolved the National Assembly on April 21 and</p>
<p>called a snap election for May 25 and June 1.</p>
<p>The dates indicate when the poll was taken. The first table is of voting</p>
<p>intentions in percentage terms. Most surveys have a margin of error of plus or</p>
<p>minus two percent.</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>			 Extreme  Communist Socialist Ecologist  RPR/UDF    Nat</p>
<p>			  left		   + allies		+ allies  Front</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> Ipsos	6-7/5    1.5	  9	  29	   6	  38	  16</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> L.Harris     5/5    2	   10	  28	   6.5	39	  14.5</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> CSA	  5-6/5    1.5	 10	  30	   4.5	40.5	13.5</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> L.Harris   2-3/5    2	   10.5	27.5	 7	  38	  15</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> BVA     30/4-3/5    2.5	 11	  26	   7.5	40	  13</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> Sofres     2-3/5    2	   10	  30	   5	  38	  15</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> IFOP	   2/5    2.5	 10	  28.5	 7	  38	  14</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> Ipsos    29/30/4    1	   10	  28	   5	  40.5	15.5</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> CSA	28-29/4    2	   10	  29	   6	  39	  14</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> L.Harris    28/4    2	   10.5	26	   7	  39	  15.5</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> L.Harris 25-26/4    2	   10	  26	   7	  40	  15</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> BVA	24-26/4    2	   10	  28	   7	  39	  14</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> Sofres   25-26/4    2.5	  9	  29.5	 5	  40	  14</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> IFOP	  25/4    2	   10	  26	   6.5	39.5	16</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> Ipsos    22-23/4    1.5	 10	  29	   5	  39.5	15</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> CSA	   22/4    1	    9	  28	   6	  43	  13</p>
<p>-------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>The second table, with a wider margin of error, is of projections in seats.</p>
<p>Some polling institutes give a range with a median figure, some give a range</p>
<p>but no median figure, some give only a median figure.</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>			 Extreme  Communist Socialist Ecologist  RPR/UDF    Nat</p>
<p>			  left		   + allies		+ allies  Front</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> Ipsos     6-7/5     0	   22	 264	   0	 290	  1</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> *L.Harris   5/5     0	   27	 224	  (**)     302	  2</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> *CSA	5-6/5     0	   21	 232	  (**)     301	  1</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> *BVA   30/4-3/5     0	   26	 232	   2	 294	  1</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> *Sofres   2-3/5     0	   26	 236	  (**)     291	  2</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> *IFOP	 2/5     0	  23-29   232-256    (**)     269-299     0-2</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> Ipsos   29-30/4     0	   26	 219	   0	 331	  1</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> *CSA    28-29/4     0	   21	 237	  (**)     296	  1</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> *BVA    24-26/4     0	   18	 238	   2	 296	  1</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> *Sofres 25-26/4     0	   23	 202	  (**)     329	  1</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> *IFOP	25/4     0	  19-25   200-220	(**)   311-331     0-3</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> Ipsos   22-23/4     0	   28	 256	   0	 292	  1</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p> *CSA	 22/4     0	   20	 201	   1	 332	  1</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>NOTE - Louis Harris only gave seat projections with its May 5 poll.</p>
<p>* poll only covers the 555 constituencies in metropolitan France, not the 22</p>
<p>seats in overseas departments and territories, most of which were held by the</p>
<p>centre-right coalition in the outgoing Assembly.</p>
<p>** no separate figure given for Ecologists, who were included in total for</p>
<p>Socialists and other left.</p>
